Project Conclusion
This project demonstrates how Linux authentication logs can be used to detect suspicious login activity. By generating failed SSH login attempts and analyzing the resulting log entries, it is possible to identify indicators of potential brute-force attacks.
Log analysis is a critical skill for security analysts because it enables early detection of malicious activity and supports incident response investigations.
